-Jean, wake up. Hurry!
-[moans]

00:12:09.496 --> 00:12:11.999 position:7% line:89% align:start
Nadia, King turned into a log.

00:12:12.032 --> 00:12:14.101 position:35% line:89% align:start
Look. Huh?

00:12:15.236 --> 00:12:16.470 position:19% line:89% align:start
Some kind of a message.

00:12:16.504 --> 00:12:18.472 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Marie] I didn't know he could
do that.

00:12:18.506 --> 00:12:20.874 position:19% line:89% align:start
Can you read it, Nadia?

00:12:20.908 --> 00:12:24.311 position:16% line:83% align:start
Well, "meow, meow, meow,
meow, meow, meow, meow,

00:12:24.345 --> 00:12:26.347 position:19% line:89% align:start
meow, meow, meow, meow

00:12:26.380 --> 00:12:30.884 position:10% line:83% align:start
meow, meow, meow, meow, meow,
meow, meow, meow, meow, meow..."

00:12:30.918 --> 00:12:33.887 position:38% line:89% align:start
[meowing]

00:12:33.921 --> 00:12:36.558 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:12:40.427 --> 00:12:43.464 position:27% line:89% align:start
[water splashing]

00:12:59.313 --> 00:13:01.081 position:27% line:89% align:start
What did he mean?

00:13:01.115 --> 00:13:02.584 position:10% line:89% align:start
"In the end, I am an animal,

00:13:02.617 --> 00:13:04.818 position:10% line:83% align:start
so I will return to the world
of animals

00:13:04.852 --> 00:13:06.887 position:30% line:83% align:start
to concentrate
on myself for a while."

00:13:07.321 --> 00:13:08.922 position:21% line:89% align:start
He ran away from us.

00:13:10.424 --> 00:13:12.293 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Jean] King!

00:13:12.326 --> 00:13:13.528 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Marie] King!

00:13:13.561 --> 00:13:14.895 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Nadia] King!

00:13:15.563 --> 00:13:17.364 position:30% line:83% align:start
I wonder where
he could have run off to.

00:13:18.198 --> 00:13:21.001 position:30% line:83% align:start
I didn't expect
the island to be so enormous.

00:13:21.035 --> 00:13:23.971 position:10% line:83% align:start
Yes. And we'll need to search
all of the caves.

00:13:24.004 --> 00:13:25.372 position:35% line:83% align:start
-The caves?
-Right.

00:13:25.406 --> 00:13:27.341 position:27% line:83% align:start
Where I found all
of the mushrooms.

00:13:27.374 --> 00:13:29.143 position:35% line:89% align:start
Mushrooms?

00:13:29.176 --> 00:13:31.912 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm sorry. I didn't
mean to bring that up.

00:13:31.945 --> 00:13:34.148 position:19% line:83% align:start
Don't you realize I was
trying to forget about that?

00:13:34.181 --> 00:13:35.916 position:24% line:89% align:start
You're infuriating.

00:13:37.017 --> 00:13:38.852 position:27% line:89% align:start
I'm really sorry.

00:13:38.886 --> 00:13:41.556 position:16% line:83% align:start
Is there any way you can
ever possibly forgive me?

00:13:41.589 --> 00:13:43.223 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'll try to make it up to you.

00:13:43.257 --> 00:13:45.560 position:7% line:83% align:start
I don't need a pathetic excuse
for a boy following me.

00:13:45.593 --> 00:13:47.061 position:30% line:89% align:start
But I'm sorry.

00:13:48.362 --> 00:13:50.331 position:7% line:89% align:start
Now we'll form search parties.

00:13:50.364 --> 00:13:52.499 position:19% line:83% align:start
Marie and I will search
through the jungle.

00:13:52.534 --> 00:13:54.602 position:27% line:83% align:start
You can look for
him up on the mountain.

00:13:56.136 --> 00:13:57.204 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh.

00:13:57.237 --> 00:13:59.139 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'm sure it will
be a really easy climb

00:13:59.173 --> 00:14:01.175 position:5% line:89% align:start
for such a heartless boy as you.

00:14:01.909 --> 00:14:03.444 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Come along, Marie.
-[Marie] I'm coming.

00:14:06.313 --> 00:14:08.550 position:30% line:83% align:start
How would being
heartless make it easy?

00:14:08.583 --> 00:14:11.885 position:27% line:89% align:start
[birds chirping]

00:14:11.919 --> 00:14:13.954 position:27% line:89% align:start
Where did he go?

00:14:14.388 --> 00:14:17.525 position:13% line:83% align:start
[gasps] I should try to use
my special powers.

00:14:17.559 --> 00:14:19.159 position:27% line:89% align:start
"Special powers"?

00:14:19.193 --> 00:14:21.995 position:10% line:83% align:start
Didn't I tell you that I have
the power to communicate

00:14:22.029 --> 00:14:24.198 position:10% line:83% align:start
-with animals using my mind?
-Oh, right.

00:14:28.268 --> 00:14:29.336 position:44% line:89% align:start
Well?

00:14:29.370 --> 00:14:31.438 position:16% line:89% align:start
No, he didn't answer me.

00:14:31.472 --> 00:14:34.441 position:24% line:83% align:start
Nadia, are you sure
that you're able to do that?

00:14:34.475 --> 00:14:37.645 position:10% line:83% align:start
His heart was broken because
I was indifferent to him.

00:14:37.679 --> 00:14:40.047 position:10% line:89% align:start
Yes. I was mean to him, too.

00:14:40.080 --> 00:14:41.382 position:35% line:89% align:start
I'm sorry.

00:14:41.415 --> 00:14:42.617 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:14:42.650 --> 00:14:45.520 position:33% line:83% align:start
Oh, I wish my
powers were a bit stronger.

00:14:45.553 --> 00:14:48.590 position:30% line:89% align:start
[wind howling]

00:14:51.693 --> 00:14:53.327 position:33% line:89% align:start
It's no use.

00:14:53.360 --> 00:14:56.063 position:19% line:83% align:start
I could find him easier
if I had an aeroplane.

00:14:56.096 --> 00:14:59.133 position:24% line:83% align:start
If I were smarter,
I could invent more things.

00:14:59.166 --> 00:15:00.334 position:27% line:83% align:start
Maybe I can build
an aeroplane

00:15:00.367 --> 00:15:02.069 position:27% line:83% align:start
that will take us
off the island.

00:15:02.102 --> 00:15:04.471 position:19% line:83% align:start
I could also use it to
take Nadia to Africa,

00:15:04.506 --> 00:15:05.973 position:13% line:89% align:start
then she'd be happy again.

00:15:08.075 --> 00:15:09.544 position:10% line:83% align:start
Of course, I'd have to build
it big enough

00:15:09.577 --> 00:15:11.178 position:10% line:89% align:start
to carry Marie and King, too,

00:15:11.211 --> 00:15:13.347 position:13% line:83% align:start
but then there's not really
any room to make a runway,

00:15:13.380 --> 00:15:14.716 position:16% line:83% align:start
so there'd be no place to
take off

00:15:14.749 --> 00:15:16.551 position:10% line:89% align:start
unless I built a water plane,

00:15:16.584 --> 00:15:18.952 position:19% line:83% align:start
in which case, we could
take off right from the ocean.

00:15:18.986 --> 00:15:20.454 position:7% line:89% align:start
So why don't I go and do that?

00:15:20.487 --> 00:15:21.656 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

00:15:21.689 --> 00:15:23.090 position:44% line:89% align:start
Good.

00:15:23.123 --> 00:15:24.592 position:35% line:89% align:start
Right. Hmm?

00:15:29.096 --> 00:15:31.932 position:35% line:89% align:start
[screaming]

00:15:35.436 --> 00:15:37.237 position:41% line:89% align:start
[thuds]

00:15:38.305 --> 00:15:40.374 position:27% line:89% align:start
[birds chirping]

00:15:40.407 --> 00:15:42.009 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Jean] Phew! That was close.

00:15:46.514 --> 00:15:49.983 position:10% line:83% align:start
Boy, I should pay a lot more
attention to where I'm walking.

00:15:52.720 --> 00:15:56.123 position:33% line:83% align:start
Look at this,
a mineral vein. Hmm?

00:15:56.156 --> 00:15:59.126 position:27% line:89% align:start
[ground rumbling]

00:15:59.159 --> 00:16:00.160 position:38% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:16:01.462 --> 00:16:03.330 position:35% line:83% align:start
Am I seeing
what I think I'm seeing?

00:16:04.264 --> 00:16:07.234 position:27% line:89% align:start
I've struck oil!

00:16:07.669 --> 00:16:10.505 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:16:37.832 --> 00:16:40.133 position:24% line:83% align:start
Thanks for waiting.
We can begin now.

00:16:40.167 --> 00:16:41.803 position:19% line:89% align:start
[wistful music playing]

00:16:41.836 --> 00:16:45.372 position:7% line:83% align:start
My latest invention uses diodes
and a permanent magnet

00:16:45.405 --> 00:16:48.141 position:24% line:83% align:start
to send super long
visual waves over the air.

00:16:48.175 --> 00:16:49.309 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Hah!
-[both gasps]

00:16:49.343 --> 00:16:51.613 position:24% line:89% align:start
[electric zapping]

00:16:51.646 --> 00:16:53.213 position:30% line:89% align:start
[both] Amazing.

00:16:53.247 --> 00:16:56.083 position:10% line:83% align:start
You certainly are a certified
genius, Jean. Great job!

00:16:58.151 --> 00:17:00.487 position:30% line:83% align:start
Next one up is
a super cool excavator

00:17:00.522 --> 00:17:03.457 position:10% line:83% align:start
that uses a heavy oil engine
and a hydraulic cylinder.

00:17:03.490 --> 00:17:04.559 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hah!

00:17:04.592 --> 00:17:07.160 position:35% line:89% align:start
[whirring]

00:17:07.194 --> 00:17:08.630 position:30% line:89% align:start
[both] Amazing.

00:17:08.663 --> 00:17:11.431 position:10% line:83% align:start
You certainly are a certified
